      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "In some localities a partly overcast night. Further warming. The avalanche danger will already exist in the early morning. This applies in particular below approximately 2500 m. <br/> <br/> As a consequence of warming and solar radiation, the natural activity of medium moist and wet avalanches will gradually increase, in particular on very steep sunny slopes. This also applies at the base of rock walls. <br/> <br/> More recent wind slabs can be released by a single winter sport participant in isolated cases in particular on shady slopes, this also applies at a distance from ridgelines, caution is to be exercised on very steep slopes at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack, when entering gullies and bowls for example.",
