      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The surface of the snowpack will soften earlier than the day before. <br/> At higher altitudes, snow cover becomes thinner and patchy; it is better at mid-altitudes, which are less exposed to the wind. <br/> The surface snowpack changes rapidly depending on the aspect and gradient: crusts of various types and thicknesses alternate. In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard crust, especially adjacent to ridgelines and in pass areas. <br/> Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on steep shady slopes. <br/> The solar radiation will give rise to increasing consolidation of the snowpack."
      },
